    Krisnawati (2016)

    krisnawati_2016.Rd

    Allometric models from Krisnawati (2016)

    Stem Volume Models

    vsk = a * dsob^b * hst^c

    • vsk [m3] - volume of the stem including bark

    • dsob [cm] - diameter of the stem, outside bark at breast height

    • hst [m] - total height of the stem

    Model Parameters

              a     b     c
1 0.0000636  1.74  1.07

    Stem Volume Models

    vsa = a * dsob^b * hst^c

    • vsa [m3] - volume of the entire stem, including top and stump

    • dsob [cm] - diameter of the stem, outside bark at breast height

    • hst [m] - total height of the stem

    Model Parameters

              a     b     c
1 0.0000542  1.08  1.04

    Stem Diameter Models

    dsoh = a * dsob^b * hst^c * hsl^d

    • dsoh [cm] - diameter of the stem, outside bark at a specified height

    • dsob [cm] - diameter of the stem, outside bark at breast height

    • hst [m] - total height of the stem

    • hsl [m] - distance from tip of stem to merchantibility limit

    Model Parameters

          a     b      c     d
1  1.38 0.868 -0.639 0.676

    Stem Diameter Models

    dsih = a * dsob^b * hst^c * hsl^d

    • dsih [cm] - diameter of the stem, inside bark at a specified height

    • dsob [cm] - diameter of the stem, outside bark at breast height

    • hst [m] - total height of the stem

    • hsl [m] - distance from tip of stem to merchantibility limit

    Model Parameters

      volume_type                                              a     b      c     d
1 merchantable volume outside bark to specified height  1.26 0.889 -0.621 0.643

    Stem Volume Models

    vsm = a * dsob^b * hst^c * (hst^d - (e * dsoh^f * dsob^g * hst^h))

    • vsm [m3] - volume of the merchantable portion of the stem

    • dsob [cm] - diameter of the stem, outside bark at breast height

    • hst [m] - total height of the stem

    • dsoh [cm] - diameter of the stem, outside bark at a specified height

    Model Parameters

              a     b     c     d     e     f     g     h
1 0.0000636  1.74 -1.28  2.35 0.326  3.48 -3.02  2.22
